Only a live armed `finalize=true` response can become a `TranscriptionFrame`; all other text is interim or withheld. Empty finals return early, duplicate final text returns early, and post-final `stop()` no longer sends another reset. This keeps committed final emission to one per armed completion path and prevents dup/empty final frames.

